headline: ROLLINS, INC. COMPLETES ACQUISTION OF SAELA HOLDINGS, LLC, A LEADING PEST MANAGEMENT COMPANY
summary: Rollins, Inc. (NYSE:ROL) ("Rollins"), a premier global consumer and commercial services company, today announced that it has acquired Saela Holdings, LLC ("Saela" or the "Company"). Saela employs more than 250 teammates and is headquartered in Orem, Utah. The Company ranks as the 23rd largest pest management company according to PCT 100 rankings with over $65 million in annual revenue. Additional transaction details will be disclosed during Rollins' first quarter 2025 earnings conference call.

headline: 3 Reasons Investors Love Rollins (ROL)
summary: While the broader market has struggled with the S&P 500 down 1.6% since October 2024, Rollins has surged ahead as its stock price has climbed by 8.4% to $54.59 per share. This performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
